---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const pageTitle = "Government Structure | Hong-Kong Republic";
const pageDescription =
  "Structure, institutions, and constitutional offices of the Government of the Hong-Kong Republic.";
---

<BaseLayout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <section>
    <h1>Government of the Hong-Kong Republic</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      The Government of the Hong-Kong Republic is established under a
      constitutional framework that ensures the separation of powers,
      institutional accountability, and continuity of governance.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Head of State</h2>
    <p>
      The President of the Hong-Kong Republic serves as the Head of State and is
      responsible for representing the Republic in external affairs, appointing
      senior officials in accordance with law, and safeguarding constitutional
      order.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Executive Authority</h2>
    <p>
      Executive power is exercised by the Government, led by the Administrative
      Prime Minister. The Government is responsible for policy execution,
      public administration, national security, and economic governance.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Legislative Authority</h2>
    <p>
      Legislative power is vested in a bicameral legislature composed of the
      Civic Assembly and the Professional Council. Together, they enact laws,
      approve budgets, and provide institutional oversight.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Judicial Authority</h2>
    <p>
      Judicial power is exercised independently by the courts of the Hong-Kong
      Republic. The judiciary safeguards the rule of law and ensures that all
      public authorities act within constitutional and legal limits.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Independent Institutions</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Financial Security Authority</li>
      <li>National Audit Office</li>
      <li>Electoral Commission</li>
      <li>Commission on Public Integrity</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .lead {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: #444;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  section {
    margin-top: 2.75rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  ul {
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
</style>
